[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man being held in custody in hospital flees in bed gown

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man arrested on suspicion of criminal damage, assaulting a police constable and breach of a court order, has escaped from custody at hospital.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Jordan Georgiou, 22, fled from Colchester General Hospital while being treated for injuries on Friday evening.
Mr Georgiou, from Clacton, is 5ft 6ins tall, with short brown hair and was dressed in a hospital gown.
An 18-year-old man and two women aged 19 and 21, all from Clacton, have been arrested for assisting an offender.
Anyone with information on Mr Georgiou's whereabouts is asked to contact police urgently.
